additional_house_rules:
Dear guests to ensure your comfort at hotel standard but low price please be considerate of our property: furniture, appliances,towels, linens.
Any stains that can not be removed after washing(blood, sunscreen, makeup, creams) will require the purchase of new ones. 
The cost will automatically be deducted from your security deposit.
Please be advised we are very strict and no concession will be made.
Also the washing machine and drier is only for owner's use. 
- Smocking allowed only outside in the backyard. This is a private house so there are no other visitors allowed in the house besides the guests.  No overnight (URL HIDDEN) parties or loud noises. Keep decency as young  children are in the premises.   
- Our house is located 20 min. drive from Midtown Manhattan. If you have your car, there is no parking regulations on our block. Public transportation is near, with access to bus than transfer to the subway. Download the MTA app so know when the buses will arrive.
- Walking distance to Dunkin Donuts, fast food, restaurants and supermarket.
- Convenient location, near La Guardia (20 minutes drive) and JFK (30 minutes drive) airports.
description:
The  studio, recently renovated, is in the basement of our family house. Its one floor down the stairs walk. Very private, with access to the backyard for smokers, fresh air or relaxing.
We are located in suburban Queens, safe and family oriented neighborhood, near schools and a church. We have a large selection of restaurants and delis, from sushi, peruvian, chinese to home cooked  style Polish food.
Also a supermarket is 10 minutes walk from our home.

The studio offers privacy , the comfort and feeling of staying at home, at the same time we take pride in offering best services for a decent price.

There is access to the backyard to relax or smoke.

Guess can contact us anytime for info.
We live upstairs so we are available 24 hours in case of late arrivals or emergencies!

There is a large selection of restaurants and diners next to our house. There is also a bakery that serves fresh coffee and their donuts are amazing. Also the polish deli offers a large selection of home cooked meals at very good prices. We sometimes get our meals from them and we are very happy with their food. Of course Dunkin Donuts is 5 minutes walk from the house.

As we encountered a few surprises from  some guests regarding the location I will try to explain again the location of our place and hopefully everyone will read it .
So again, to limit the surprise, our studio is located in suburban Queens, 20 minutes drive from Manhattan or about 45 minutes by commute. The Bus that we advise our guests to take is Q59 which is 5 minute walk from our home. The Bus stops at Grand street, right by the L subway which will take you to 14 street Union Square in Manhattan. 
There are other Bus lines like Q58 which is very reliable,  7 minute walk from us. It takes you to the R subway than Manhattan(There are about 8 stops to the city).
Also Q 39, 5 min walk from our house. It takes you to the # 7 subway in Sunnyside on 48th Ave and 47 st.
My husband and I offer rides to the subway station anytime our schedule permits it. We are always available for any questions.
I strongly recommend  for our guests to download the MTA app for real times of buses and trains.
Like I mentioned the commute from our home to Manhattan is about 45 minutes in real time!
Bus line - Q59, 2 blocks from our house, with transfer to L train  that takes you to 14 street Union Square. Also available , 5 minutes walk, Q58 with transfer to the R train. Commute to the city usually takes 45 minutes with bus and train.
Hope this helps and please feel free to contact us with any questions!
Regards, Mihaela!

There is no A/C. There are 2 fans if needed. 
There is a hot plate for light cooking . There is a microwave,fridge, coffee maker and hot water maker.
No pets allowed! Our child is highly allergic to pets(dogs and cats).
